profile_positions.description:
Arup is succesfull in the European region because we add value and outstanding knowledge about bridge design and engineering to the existing bridge market. 

We have a growing business, but we stand for quality and reliability so we are looking fo the best qualified people who fit into our firm.

As an Associate Director I am responsible for managing and directing:

1. The Bridge practice (skills & people) within Continental Europe;

2. The Technical & Project Management of Managing Contractor project Renovation 8 steel Bridges;

From January 2010 till December 2010 I acted as associate and I was responsible for:


1. Technical Management, JV Managing Contractor for:

Leading and managing the technical assessment, design of local and global strengthening measures, procurement and backoffice during construction of 8 steel Highway Bridge: Muiderbrug, Scharbergbrug, Beek, Suurhoffbrug, Galecopperbruggen, Kreekrak, 1st brug bij Ewijk and v. Van Brienenoordbrug.

2. The Bridge discipline within the Netherlands;

3. The Bridge Skills Network within Continental Europe;
